Package: mirhostgenes
Type: Package
Title: mirhostgenes: putting miRNAs into genomic context
Version: 0.99.0
Author: J. Rainer
Maintainer: Johannes Rainer <johannes.rainer@eurac.edu>
URL: https://github.com/jotsetung/mirhostgenes
Imports: methods, Biobase, DBI, RSQLite, GenomicFeatures, GenomeInfoDb,
	 AnnotationDbi, S4Vectors, IRanges
Depends: BiocGenerics, ensembldb (>= 0.99.8), GenomicRanges
Suggests: BiocStyle, knitr, rmarkdown, RUnit, MirhostDb.Hsapiens.v75.v20
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Description: This package provides functionality to define host genes for all miRNAs
	     of a species and build and use the corresponding database and annotation
	     packages. miRNAs are frequently encoded in introns of transcripts from, mostly
	     protein coding, genes and exons of non-coding transcripts/genes. Such miRNAs are
	     frequently co-transcribed with these host transcripts and their expression
	     correlates to some extent with the expression of the mRNA from these primary
	     transcription units.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Collate: Classes.R Generics.R Methods.R Methods-Filter.R dbhelpers.R makehostgenedb.R
	 utils.R
biocViews: Genetics, AnnotationData

